ht to play, for improving the quality of children's play, enhancing their play satisfaction and participation, and reducing play deprivation. Written in a lay-person language, providing ready-to-use information, this book is for parents, teachers, rehabilitation professionals, toy manufacturers, policy makers and in general for all of those interested in the topic of play for children with disabilities. This publication results from the research and work of a transdisciplinary team, all participants in the COST Action "LUDI - Play for Children with Disabilities". ABSTRACTING & INDEXING Guidelines for supporting children with disabilities' play is covered by the following services: Baidu Scholar​ CNKI Scholar (China National Knowledge Infrastructure)​ Dimensions​ DOAB (Directory of Open Access Books) ExLibris Google Books Google Scholar Naviga ReadCube​ Semantic Scholar ​ TDOne (TDNet)​ WorldCat (OCLC)​ X-MOL​  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY-NC-ND 3.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc-nd/3.0 uhttps://www.degruyter.com/dg/page/open-access-policy  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2023) 7aEDUCATION / Educational Psychology.2bisacsh  aPlay for the sake of play, Inclusion, Impairment, Children's rights, Special education, Early intervention, Occupational Therapy, Environmental factors, Toys.1 aBesio, Serenella, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBianquin, Nicole, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut1 aBianquin, Nicole, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBonarini, Andrea, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBulgarelli, Daniela, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaprino, Francesca, econtributor.4ctb4https